Former Everton midfielder Andy van der Meyde rates Zlatan Ibrahimovic alongside Cristiano Ronaldo and Lionel Messi as the world's greatest players.

The Dutchman, who had a troubled stay on Merseyside after being signed by David Moyes in 2005, played with Ibrahimovic during the Sweden striker's time at Ajax between 2001 and 2003.

Although Messi and Ronaldo are widely regarded as the game's standout players, Van der Meyde insists that the Paris Saint Germain forward deserves to be recognised in the same company.

